$ SQL Server function: convert

`convert` returns the value of an expression in a different → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types[data type].

code {
convert(datatype        , expression       )
convert(datatype(length), expression       )
convert(datatype        , expression, style)
code }

{ Simple example

  gh|about-MSSQL|/t-sql/functions/convert.sql||

}

sa:

  The → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/functions/cast[`cast()`] and → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/functions/format[`format`] functions.

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/functions
